  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Although outpatient surgery is increasing in France, particularly in paediatrics, compliance&#xD;
      with analgesics prescriptions and pain management on return home remain poorly controlled&#xD;
      parameters, although they are essential for optimal care. This is due, among other things, to&#xD;
      parents' lack of knowledge and fears about the medicines prescribed to them. The paediatric&#xD;
      anaesthesia unit of the Rouen University Hospital has set up a website for families to&#xD;
      improve understanding of and compliance with the prescription of painkillers and thus improve&#xD;
      the management of postoperative pain.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
